<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1909/515396-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.The auditions are scheduled on Saturdays and Sundays in Lagos and are opened to both male and female participants who are above 18 years of age and single. The TV show, currently enjoying massive viewership in other African countries including Kenya and Zambia will be aired from October 2019 exclusively on StarTimes, with a cash prize of N300,000 available for the successfully matched couple.Kunmi Balogun, public relations manager of StarTimes noted that “The show follows the general format of the well-known dating show which originated from China called, If You Are the One. During the show, a male guest introduces himself and tries to impress a group of female participants. The women can opt-out of the selection process if they don’t like the guy, and he picks the woman he wants to date from the ones who are left after a series of questioning.“Hello Mr. Right is for anyone who is single and searching – it’s a fun way to meet interesting people and maybe find that special one. We are now calling on interested, potential contestants to come for the auditions for a chance to find love,’’ he said.